An ANC meeting to nominate a ward councillor descended into chaos this weekend. The governing party is condemning the violence which left dozens injured. ANC's Limpopo Secretary, Soviet Lekganyane, has more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - An African National Congress (ANC) meeting to nominate a ward councillor descended into chaos this weekend. READ: ANC condemns senior members' behaviour The governing party is condemning the violence which left dozens injured. The ANC in Waterberg has now halted all party activities in the Lephalale subregion until further notice.